⚔️ Aether Blade: Fragmented (Updated)
Genre: Top-Down Action Rogue-lite
Engine: Godot 4.4.1
Platform: PC

🎮 Core Gameplay Loop
Fight → Loot → Fight → Upgrade → Die → Repeat
- Enter a room, defeat all enemies to progress
- Collect Gold and Blue Mana Shards
- Spend Gold at shops for temporary boosts
- After dying, receive Shards based on performance
- Use Shards for permanent companion/equipment unlocks via Gacha

🧙 The Player: The Water Mage
Abilities:
- Normal Attack: Fires a water ball (no cooldown)
- Passive (Mana Overload): Every 4th attack fires 3 water balls in a
  parabolic burst instead of 1
- Skill E (Tidal Field): Summons a water circle for 5 seconds.
  Heals player 10 HP/sec, damages enemies inside. CD: 10s
- Skill Q (King's Call): Summons up to 5 water slimes (1 every 2s)
  that chase enemies. Grants +20% attack for 30s. Slimes mirror
  player stats at 30%. CD: 45s
- Dash (Shift): Double dash with invincibility frames, water splash
  effect. Each charge recovers after 3.5s
- Hold Attack + Move Mouse: Places ice spikes on map (max 10,
  or 25 with Frozen Arsenal modifier)
- R Key: Recalls all placed ice spikes, dealing pass-through damage
  to enemies on return path

📊 Player Stats
HP: 100 | Base ATK: 10 | Crit Rate: 5% | Crit DMG: 150%
Move Speed: 300 | Energy Max: 100

🌀 Rogue-lite Systems

🏠 Room System
- 3 rooms (room1, room2, room3) randomized per run
- Each room has enemy zones with auto-spawning enemies
- Room clear triggers portal appearance
- Portal gives choice: End Run or Continue (with death penalty risk)

💰 Economy
Gold: Dropped by enemies (Normal: 3-10, Elite: 11-20, Boss: 0)
     Used for shop purchases
Blue Mana Shards:
- Room first clear: 200 shards
- Room repeat clear: 50 shards
- Boss kill: 40 shards
- Iron Will modifier bonus: +30 per room
- Skip modifier: doubles run rewards
- Used for Gacha pulls

⚠️ Death Penalty
- Dying loses 10-40% of run-earned gold and shards
- Scales: 10% per room cleared, capped at 40%
- Only affects earnings from current run, not pre-run inventory

🎲 Modifier System (chosen each room after loading)
Current Room Modifiers:
1. Blood Money: +80% gold, -5% max HP/3s DoT
2. Glass Cannon: +200% damage, enemies 30% faster
3. Plague Pact: Player and enemies take 5% max HP damage/3s
4. Shielded Fury: +20% max HP shield per kill, +10% dmg while shielded
5. Inverted Soul: Healing damages, damage heals
6. Worthy Opponents: All enemies become elite, +30% rewards
7. Living on Edge: Start at 1HP, gain 10% max HP shield per kill
8. High Stakes: Double rewards, guaranteed boss spawn
9. Frozen Arsenal: Ice spike cap increased to 25

Whole Run Modifiers:
1. Berserker: +100% damage, max HP reduced to 30%
2. On a Roll: +7% attack per kill, resets on hit
3. Endless Growth: +10% damage per kill, no cap
4. Iron Will: Cannot heal, +30 shards per room

Special (10% chance):
- Skip: No modifier, double rewards at end of room

🌍 Map Events (triggered after modifier choice, current room only)
- None (50% chance): No effect
- Rainstorm (12.5%): +700% attack/HP, +400% speed, rain visual,
  slimes are 1.4x bigger and 3x stronger
- Extra Darkness (12.5%): Spotlight radius shrinks
- Blood Moon (12.5%): All enemies +20% HP/ATK/Speed, red tint
- Frost Zone (12.5%): Slippery movement, snow visual, blue tint

👾 Enemy System
Enemies use StatsComponent for all stats.
Zone System: EnemyZone (Polygon2D shapes) + ZoneDetector component
GroupZone: Auto-injects ZoneDetector into child enemies

Enemy Types:
- Glitch (Normal): Melee chaser, low HP
- Bird/Vulture (Elite): Fly-circle + air wave attack pattern,
  air-type color effects
- Golem (Boss): Two-phase boss
  Phase 1: Maintains range, channels stone burst every 4s,
           backs up + shields when player gets too close
  Phase 2: Continuous stone rain, faster when player is close
  Transition: On phase 1 death → 5 incubations scatter on map.
             Player has 30s to destroy them. Each destroyed
             incubation = 20% less HP in phase 2. If none
             destroyed = full HP phase 2.

Spawner System (ZoneSpawner + RoomSpawner):
- Normal zone: 4 normal enemies
- Elite zone: 2 elite enemies
- Boss zone: 1 boss + 2 normal
- Mixed (20% chance): 1 boss + 1 elite OR 1 elite + 2 normal
- Guaranteed 2 elites per room
- Boss guaranteed every 5 rooms or 10% random chance

🐉 Companion System
- Permanent unlocks via Gacha (Blue Mana Shards)
- One companion active per run
- Companions fly beside the player when equipped (scene-based)
- Provide passive stat buffs (HP, ATK, Crit Rate, Crit DMG, Speed)
- Duplicate pulls → Companion Essence (used for future upgrades)

Current Companions:
- Lirien: +15 ATK buff. Passive: heals 15 HP every 20s,
  blocks one killing blow (4 min CD)
- Grumoss: +30 HP buff. Passive: grants shield every 20s
  (20% of ATK), up to 20% DMG reduction when not taking hits
  (1% per 5s, resets on damage taken)

Companion Resources: res://resources/companions/
Companion Art: res://assets/companion/

🎰 Gacha System
- Max pity: 70 pulls per banner
- 5-star rate: 1% pulls 1-50, +2.5% per pull from 51+
- Pull 70: Guaranteed 5-star banner highlight
- Every 10th pull: Guaranteed 4-star
- 4-star base rate: 6%
- Separate pity tracker per banner (companion vs equipment)
- 5-star companions trigger fullscreen reveal animation with art

Banners:
- Companion Banner: 5-star companions (Lirien, Grumoss)
- Equipment Banner: 5-star equipment (coming soon)

Pull Results:
- 5-star: Sand gold card, fullscreen white-gold flash + companion art reveal
- 4-star: Purple card, amber glow effect
- 3-star: Dusty grey card (Aether Dust)

4-star Pool (auto-loaded from resource folders):
Items: res://resources/items/
- Large Health Potion (heal_hp)
- Large Speed Potion (buff_speed)
- Large Attack Buff (buff_attack)
- Large Health Buff (buff_health)
- Massive Crit Rate Buff (buff_critrate)
- Massive Crit DMG Buff (buff_critdamage)

Equipment: res://resources/equipment/
- Apprentice Headgear, Cloak, Ring, Shoes

5-star Equipment: res://resources/equipment_5star/

🎒 Bag System
Accessible as a popup from Main Menu (no scene change).
Three tabs:

Companion Tab:
- Active companion display (icon, name, buff description)
- Companion Essence counter (upgrades coming soon)
- Grid of owned companions (5 columns)
- Click card → popup with stats, passive info, Equip/Unequip

Equipment Tab:
- Active gear panel (4 slots: Headgear, Cloak, Ring, Shoes)
- Click active gear → popup to unequip
- Bag grid separated by slot type with headers
- Click bag card → popup to equip

Items Tab:
- Grid grouped by category (Heal, Attack, Speed, Health,
  Crit Rate, Crit Damage)
- Category headers auto-hide when empty
- Click card → popup with description and Use button
- Companion Essence hidden here, shown in Companion tab

🏪 In-Run Shop (every 3 rooms, uses Gold)
- Health Elixir: Restores 30% HP
- Sharpening Stone: +2 Base Damage (until death)
- Haste Potion: +10% attack speed (rest of run)

🏛️ Technical Architecture

Autoloads (res://globals/):
- PlayerStats: Final stats (base + equipment + companion + item buffs)
  Handles: recalculate(), take_damage(), heal(), apply_item(),
           gain_energy(), spend_energy(), timed buff countdown,
           clear_run_buffs() on run end
- PlayerInventory: Gold, shards, items dictionary, bag_equipment array,
  active_equipment dictionary (4 slots), companions_owned array,
  active_companion slot
- GachaSystem: Pull logic, pity tracking (per banner), pool auto-loading
  from resource folders, 5-star/4-star/3-star result generation
- PassiveManager: Companion passive logic per process tick
  Lirien: heal timer, death block cooldown
  Grumoss: shield timer, damage reduction accumulator,
           damage notification hook
- CursorManager: Custom cursor (50x50), applied globally
- RunState: Run progress, kill tracking, reward tracking,
            journal stats, death penalty calculation
- ModifierSystem: Active modifier tracking, effect application,
                  kill/hit/heal hooks, enemy stat modification
- EventSystem: Map event rolling, activation, frost zone physics,
               spotlight control, enemy stat modification

Components (res://scenes/characters/):
- StatsComponent: Shared HP, ATK, Speed, Crit, Energy node
  Used by all enemies. Players use PlayerStats autoload instead.
- ZoneDetector: Enemy zone awareness, return-home behavior,
                obstacle avoidance, healing on return
- SkillManager: Player skill cooldowns and casting

Resources:
- res://resources/items/          → ItemData .tres files
- res://resources/equipment/      → EquipmentData .tres (4-star)
- res://resources/equipment_5star/→ EquipmentData .tres (5-star)
- res://resources/companions/     → CompanionData .tres files
- res://resources/modifiers/      → RunModifier .tres files

Key Classes:
- ItemData (extends Resource): item_name, description, icon,
  effect_type (enum), effect_value, effect_duration (seconds,
  0 = permanent for run)
- EquipmentData (extends Resource): equipment_name, slot (enum:
  headgear/cloak/ring/shoes), icon, bonus stats (health, attack,
  crit_rate, crit_damage, speed)
- CompanionData (extends Resource): companion_name, description,
  icon, full_art, companion_scene (PackedScene, for fly-beside
  visual), buff_type (enum), buff_value, buff_description,
  passive_type (enum: none/lirien_passive/grumoss_passive)

Key Scenes:
- res://scenes/globals/       → autoload scripts
- res://scenes/characters/player/ → player + skills
- res://scenes/characters/enemies/ → enemy scenes
- res://scenes/ui/            → HUD, modifier picker, portal choice,
                                 end run screen, event banner
- res://scenes/game/          → main_menu, pull_scene, bag_scene,
                                 rooms/room1, room2, room3
- res://shaders/              → spotlight shader
- res://scripts/effects/      → visual effect scripts
                                (rain, snow, dash splash,
                                 ice hit, water hit ripple)
- res://assets/companion/     → companion art per folder
- res://assets/ui/            → cursor, UI assets

🖥️ UI Scenes

Main Menu (res://scenes/game/main_menu.tscn):
- Buttons: Play, Pull, Bag (popup), Enemies (coming soon), Quit
- Gold and Blue Shards display (live from PlayerInventory)
- Meteor shower background effect
- Bag opens as popup (no scene change)

Pull Scene (res://scenes/game/pull_scene.tscn):
- Two banners: Companion and Equipment
- Slide transition between banners (fade + cubic ease)
- Spinning rune circles ambient effect (full screen, sand gold)
- Per-banner pity label (Pity: X/70)
- Pull 1x (160 shards) and 10x (1600 shards) buttons
- Details popup per banner
- Result grid (5 columns, color-coded by rarity)
- 5-star companion: fullscreen white-gold flash + art reveal (4s)
- Sand/desert color theme throughout

Bag Scene (res://scenes/game/bag_scene.tscn):
- Opens as popup from Main Menu
- Spinning rune circles ambient effect (brighter for black bg)
- Three tabs: Companion, Equipment, Items
- All lists displayed as 5-column grids with icon slots
- Popup card system for equip/unequip/use actions
- Equipment separated by slot type with headers
- Items separated by effect category with color-coded borders
